<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Despite widespread reports in the literature, we were able to confirm the presence of this species (Fig. 5B) in Papua New Guinea, Sri Lanka, and Thailand, only. In the phylogenetic tree, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. furfuracea" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="furfuracea">P. furfuracea</taxonomicName>
forms a clade with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. dolichospora" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="dolichospora">P. dolichospora</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. foliatella" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="foliatella">P. foliatella</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1).
</paragraph>
